Sentencas: In this paper, a detailed one-dimension transient elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with syngas based on button cell geometry is developed.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: The model, which incorporates anodic elementary heterogeneous reactions, electrochemical kinetics, electrodes microstructure and complex transport phenomena (momentum, mass and charge transport) in positive electrode vertical bar electrolyte vertical bar negative electrode (PEN), is validated with experimental performance for various syngas compositions at 750,800 and 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: The comparisons show that the simulation results agree reasonably well with the experimental data.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: Then the model is applied to analyze the effects of temperature and operation voltage on polarizations in each component of PEN, electronic current density in both electrodes and species concentrations distributions in anode.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: The numerical results of carbon deposition simulation indicate that higher temperature and lower operation voltage are helpful to reduce the possibility of carbon deposition on Ni surfaces by Bouduard reactions.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: Furthermore, a sensitivity analysis of cell performance on syngas composition is performed for the typical syngas from entrained-flow coal gasifier and natural methane thermochemical reforming processes.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas

Sentencas: The cell performance increases with the increasing of effective compositions (e.g. H-2 and CO) in syngas and the large N-2 content introduced by using air as oxidant leads to significant deterioration of performance.
Titulo: Elementary reaction kinetic model of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell fueled with syngas
